## Photography & Imagery

### When Images Exist

- **Moody, textural, natural** — Not sterile stock photography
- **Editorial compositions** — Hands, products, lifestyle shots
- **Botanical/nature elements** — Serene, organic feel
- **Warm lighting** — Avoid harsh, clinical lighting
- **Artistic product shots** — Products as objects of beauty

### Photography-Forward Design

Images and text interact. Don't silo them:
- Text overlaid on images (with appropriate contrast)
- Images extending beyond containers
- Overlapping content blocks on images
- Full-bleed photography for impact

### Avoid

- Generic stock photography ("people shaking hands")
- Clinical/sterile imagery
- Harsh lighting
- Isolated floating elements
- Images that feel like afterthoughts

